Statistical learning

Zeqi Li

2024-11-21

Import data

bwt_df = read_csv("data/birthweight.csv") |> 
  janitor::clean_names() |> 
  mutate(babysex = case_match(babysex,
                              1 ~ "male",
                              2 ~ "female"),
         babysex = fct_infreq(babysex),
         frace = case_match(frace,
                            1 ~ "white",
                            2 ~ "black",
                            3 ~ "asian",
                            4 ~ "puerto rican",
                            8 ~ "other"),
         frace = fct_infreq(frace),
         mrace = case_match(mrace,
                            1 ~ "white",
                            2 ~ "black",
                            3 ~ "asian",
                            4 ~ "puerto rican",
                            8 ~ "other"),
         mrace = fct_infreq(mrace))

Construct inputs for glmnet

x = model.matrix(bwt ~ .,
                 data = bwt_df)[, -1]
y = bwt_df |> pull(bwt)

Fit LASSO with several \(\lambda\)

lambda = 10^seq(-2, 2.75, by = 0.1)

lasso_fit = glmnet(x = x,
                   y = y,
                   lambda = lambda)

lasso_cv = cv.glmnet(x = x,
                     y = y,
                     lambda = lambda)

lambda_opt = lasso_cv[["lambda.min"]]

LASSO plot

lasso_fit |> 
  broom::tidy() |> 
  filter(term != "(Intercept)") |> 
  select(term, 
         lambda,
         estimate) |> 
  complete(term, 
           lambda,
           fill = list(estimate = 0)) |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = lambda,
             y = estimate,
             group = term,
             color = term)) +
    geom_line()

Look at CV results

lasso_cv |> 
  broom::tidy() |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = log(lambda, 10),
             y = estimate)) +
  geom_point()

Fit LASSO with the optimal lambda

final_lasso_fit = glmnet(x = x,
                         y = y,
                         lambda = lambda_opt)

final_lasso_fit |> 
  broom::tidy()

Visualize

pokemon_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = hp,
             y = speed)) +
  geom_point()

Fit K-means

kmeans_fit = kmeans(x = pokemon_df,
                    centers = 3)

Plot K-means results

pokemon_df = broom::augment(kmeans_fit, pokemon_df)

pokemon_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = hp,
             y = speed,
             color = .cluster)) +
  geom_point()
